      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WATCH HER WIN (6) found the frame for the second consecutive time when narrowly beaten into second last time out (17.52) over 300m at Taree Super Track. Safe beginner but tricky box to overcome. Looks suited here and big improvement expected. ULTRA VIOLET (1) jumped cleanly last start and led all the way (23.01) at Richmond in a Grade 5 over 401m. Solid formlines coming through her last run. Has definite claims. MAGIC SILVER (2) was safely held last time out, finishing eighth at Taree Super Track over 300m behind Zipping Tanaka (18.48) in a Grade 5. Was a winner the start prior. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Expected to feature in the finish. THEO THE GREAT (7) was well fancied last time on the back of some sparkling form, which included a three-start winning streak, but could only manage fourth (19.99) at Gunnedah. Safe beginner but wide box to overcome and will need some luck.",
